#: ../../../release_details/9.4/adios2-vtx-reader-changes.md:1
msgid "ADIOS2 VTX reader changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/adios2-vtx-reader-changes.md:3
msgid "Fix cell data with time in ADIOS2 VTX reader"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/adios2-vtx-reader-changes.md:5
msgid ""
"The ADIOS2 VTX reader supports cell data. However, the previous "
"implementation of the reader hard-coded the cell data to be static so that "
"only the first time step was read. The new implementation checks the time "
"dimension for cell (and point) fields and will automatically read a field "
"over time if available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/adios2-vtx-reader-changes.md:10
msgid "Fixed ADIOS2 VTX reader error reporting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/adios2-vtx-reader-changes.md:12
msgid ""
"The ADIOS2 VTX reader previously reported errors by throwing exceptions.  "
"This causes lots of problems with VTK and programs that use it such as "
"ParaView because exceptions are not expected. They are not caught or "
"recovered from. Instead, it just causes applications to crash without "
"warning. The ADIOS2 VTX reader now properly reports errors by calling "
"`vtkErrorMacro` and returning 0 from its process request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/adios2-vtx-reader-changes.md:18
msgid "Add protection for missing arrays in ADIOS2 VTX reader"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/adios2-vtx-reader-changes.md:20
msgid ""
"Previously, when the ADIOS2 VTX reader read in most data arrays from the "
"ADIOS2 file, it would silently leave a null array if that array did not "
"exist. This opened up the likely consequence of the program later crashing "
"when the reader attempted to use this array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/adios2-vtx-reader-changes.md:24
msgid ""
"Instead, the reader now reports an error when an array it attempts to read "
"in is missing. This prevents subsequent problems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/adios2-vtx-reader-changes.md:27
msgid "IOADIOS2 VTX reader supports non-MPI builds"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/adios2-vtx-reader-changes.md:29
msgid "The ADIOS2 VTX reader can now be built with or without MPI enabled."
msgstr ""
